      • compare11WithTemplate

        public int compare11WithTemplate(byte[] templateData,
                                 MutableBoolean bMatched)
        Compare the the template from the live stream image with the input iris templates.
        Parameters:
        templateData - The input template to compare.
        bMatched - The matching result between the input template with the template from the live stream image. The value is "true" when comparison distance is less than a specified value in library (matched), and "false" when not matched.
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure

      • compareTemplates

        public int compareTemplates(byte[] tpl1,
                            byte[] tpl2,
                            Float outDistance)
        Compare 2 iris templates. The distance to tell how similarity these 2 iris templates are. The lower distance is the more similarity.
        Parameters:
        tpl1 - The fist template to be compared.
        tpl2 - The second template to be compared.
        outDistance - Distance returned from comparison results.
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure

        Float

      • identifyCapture

        public int identifyCapture(java.util.ArrayList<MatchResult> resultList)
        This is blocking function. It will start iris sensor to capture iris images and compare the template generated from the current captured image with the templates belonging to each user ID in the gallery. Before calling this function, users have to make sure the captured image is available.
        Parameters:
        resultList - contains a list of matched comparison results between the templates generated from captured image and each enrolled template in the gallery. Each result consists of a user ID and a comparison distance less than a specified value in library.
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure
        See Also:
        MatchResult

        resultList - contains a list of matched comparison results between the input template and each enrolled template in the gallery. Each result consists of a user ID and a comparison distance less than a specified value in library.
        Returns:

      • verifyCapture

        public int verifyCapture(java.lang.String enrollId,
                         MutableBoolean matched)
        This is blocking function. It will start iris sensor to capture iris images and compare the template generated from the currently captured iris image(s) with the templates belonging to userID in the gallery. Before calling this function, users have to make sure that captured image is available.
        Parameters:
        enrollId - The enroll ID that has enrolled irises to be matched with captured iris images
        matched - Matching result between the template generated from the current captured image and the template belonging to userId. The value is "true" when comparison distance is less than a specified value in library (matched), and "false" when not matched.
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure

      • enrollCapture

        public int enrollCapture(java.lang.String userId)
        Enrolls template generated from the latest captured image. If the user ID already exists, the template will be added to the existing one. If it does not exist, an entry for it will be created in the gallery.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user ID to enroll
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure

      • enrollTemplate

        public int enrollTemplate(java.lang.String userId,
                          DataBuffer templateData)
        Enrolls with input template. If the user ID already exists, the template will be added to the existing one. If it does not exist, an entry for it will be created in the gallery.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user ID to enroll
        templateData - The template data to enroll.
        Returns:
        values in GemResult. GemResult.IDDK_OK if success and other values for failure

      • unenroll

        public int unenroll(java.lang.String enrollId)

        Returns:

      • getAllIDs

        public int getAllIDs(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> userIds)
        Gets all user ids in the gallery.
        Parameters:
        userIds - Contains a list of user IDs in the gallery. Users need to keep track and maintain these IDs, because any operation performed on the gallery will refer to these IDs instead of the enrolled templates.
        Returns:
        Return Code | Description
        ---------- | ----------
        RC_OK | Success. RC_FAILED_CONNECT_TO_SERVER | Can not connect to device. RC_STORAGE_GET_USER_ITEM_FAILED | Failed to get user item, corresponding to userId, from gallery repository. RC_STORAGE_FAILED | The general error. Failed to execute a method or function.

      • getEnrolleeTemplate

        public int getEnrolleeTemplate(java.lang.String userId,
                               DataBuffer templateData)
        Get template of enrolled user.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user ID to get template.
        templateData - A data structure that will hold the returned iris template.
        Returns:
        Return Code | Description
        ---------- | ----------
        RC_OK | Success. RC_FAILED_CONNECT_TO_SERVER | Can not connect to device. RC_RC_FIC_CAPTURE_BUSY | Iris Capture service is in progress for capturing iris images. RC_RC_FIC_NO_FRAME_AVAILABLE | No capture frame available.

      • getResultTemplates

        public int getResultTemplates(DataBuffer left,
